text: Greene County is a county in the U.S. state of New York. As of the 2020 census, the population was 47,931. The county seat is Catskill. The county's name is in honor of the American Revolutionary War general Nathanael Greene. Greene County was founded on March 3, 1800. == References == Category:1800s establishments in New York (state) Category:1800 establishments in the United States Category:New York (state) counties
